MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
GS-07
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-06 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: *Experience and understanding of numerous federal statutes affecting military criminal law, primarily, but not limited to, the Uniform Code of Military Justice, U.S. Navy regulations, and Judge Advocate General Manual;
*Experience performing assignments, independently without specific instruction, according to policies, previous experience, and accepted practice;
*Experience creating and composing a variety of correspondence for diverse reasons, including official Navy correspondence (military and civilian format), military message traffic and legal memoranda;
*Experience examining all services, disciplinary, and medical records as appropriate to evaluate a case for separation processing Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website:
https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
